OL,5, At the Barn Pub near Rugby, the drinks 
OL,6, are ready to be served, but unless lots
OL,7, of customers arrive, staff leave early.
OL,9,F"If no regulars come in, we close      
OL,10,Fearly," the chef says. "It costs to    
OL,11,Fkeep this building heated."            
OL,13,FThe Barn Pub is not alone. A survey    
OL,14,Ffrom the British Beer and Pub          
OL,15,FAssociation, seen by the BBC, suggested
OL,16,Fmost pubs are thinking of cutting down 
OL,17,Ftrading hours over the winter.         
OL,19,FThe industry is grappling with energy  
OL,20,Fbills and staff shortages.             
